commit.message: Normalise line endings (from ocaml/ocaml)

Add github-linguist attributes

num is written in OCaml, not Standard ML!

Build with -warn-error +A only in the dev profile

Use Dune's env stanza to apply -warn-error +A only in the (default) dev
profile.

The Makefile now recognises an equivalent PROFILE variable which should
be either be auto, dev, or release. If the build tree includes a .git
directory then the dev profile is assumed.

CI explicitly specifies PROFILE=dev and the opam installation explicitly
specifies PROFILE=release.

Remove toplevel/Makefile

It's no longer required (and broken) since PR#29.

It causes difficulties with Js_of_OCaml and especially with Wasm_of_OCaml.

commit.message:
Remove uses of globally-allocated nat temporaries (#25)

Either allocate temp at each use, or remove the need for temporary space
by using a simpler algorithm.

This should make the Num library safe for domains and for threads.
